  "prompt": "What is a good website for free books?",
  "response": "There are several websites where you can access free books. Some popular ones include:\n\n1. **Project Gutenberg**: This site offers over 60,000 free eBooks, mostly classical literature that is in the public domain.\n2. **Open Library**: An initiative of the Internet Archive, it provides access to millions of free eBooks, including modern works with a lending system.\n3. **Google Books**: While not all books are free, Google Books provides extensive previews and sometimes full access to a range of titles.\n4. **LibriVox**: Offers free audiobooks of public domain works, read by volunteers from around the world.\n5. **ManyBooks**: Has over 50,000 free eBooks available for download, including both public domain classics and newer titles by independent authors.\n6. **BookBoon**: Specializes in free eBooks for students and business professionals, primarily educational and career-related.\n7. **Feedbooks**: Offers a mix of free original books and public domain works.\n\nThese websites are a great starting point for finding free books in various genres and formats.",
